 <text>
  <front>
   <head>SOLITUDE. A SONG. TO LADY COVENTRY'S MINUET.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">SWEET companion of the muse!</l>
     <l n="2" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Gentle Solitude! appear,</l>
     <l n="3" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">All thy calm content infuse,</l>
     <l n="4" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Soften anguish, banish care:</l>
     <l n="5" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Lead me, O majestic queen!</l>
     <l n="6" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Thro' the aromatic scene:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Nature's copied here by art,</l>
     <l n="8" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Joyful we the fraud confess,</l>
     <l n="9" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Yet so well performs her part,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">'Tis but Nature's better dress:</l>
     <l n="11" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Solitude here fix my seat,</l>
     <l n="12" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Here in Cowley's soft retreat.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Lay me in the silent mead,</l>
     <l n="14" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Where the murmuring river flows,</l>
     <l n="15" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Where the elm expands the shade,</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">And each rising beauty blows:</l>
     <l n="17" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">There I'll say, in peace of mind,</l>
     <l n="18" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">"Empty greatness fall behind."</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="19" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Teach thy votary all the powers</l>
     <l n="20" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Of each plant, and every tree,</l>
     <l n="21" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Tell how short-liv'd are the flowers,</l>
     <l n="22" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Bring the moral home to me,</l>
     <l n="23" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Bid me fleeting life despise,</l>
     <l n="24" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Make me humble, make me wise.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="25" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Pride within my lowly cell</l>
     <l n="26" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Never yet up-rear'd her head,</l>
     <l n="27" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Solitude, with thee I'll dwell!</l>
     <l n="28" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Pride with me is long since dead:</l>
     <l n="29" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Cold to Pleasure, deaf to Praise,</l>
     <l n="30" met="+-|+-|+-|+" line_length="7">Here I wish to end my days.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
